Modificar el .csproj: abrir el Products.API.csproj y agregar lo siguiente, en property group quedando asi:
<PropertyGroup>// genera XML comments para swagger
  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
  <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
  <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>

  <GenerateDocumentationFile>true</GenerateDocumentationFile>
  <NoWarn>$(NoWarn);1591</NoWarn>
</PropertyGroup>

En el program.cs agregar: using System.Reflection;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

builder.Services.AddSwaggerGen(options => // el swagger muestra descripcion, summaries y se ve mas profesional
{
    options.SwaggerDoc("v1", new OpenApiInfo
    {
        Title = "Products API",
        Version = "v1",
        Description = "Microservicio de productos para ECommerce",
        Contact = new OpenApiContact
        {
            Name = "Grupo CAI",
            Email = "grupo@uba.ar"
        }
    });

    var xmlFilename =
        $"{Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly().GetName().Name}.xml";

    options.IncludeXmlComments(
        Path.Combine(AppContext.BaseDirectory, xmlFilename));
});

